      <h1>Homelab</h1>

      <div class="box">
        <h3>Architectuur</h3>
        <pre>
Internet
  ↓ (Public IPv4)
Ziggo modem (bridge)
  ↓
TP-Link Deco (router, NAT + port forward 80/443)
  ↓
Raspberry Pi (Docker)
  ├─ Nginx Proxy Manager (TLS / reverse proxy)
  └─ Containers (whoami, portfolio, etc.)
        </pre>
        <p>Principes: <strong>least exposure</strong> (alleen 80/443), services intern via Docker network, publiek via NPM.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="box" style="margin-top:14px">
        <h3>Stack</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><code>Docker</code> voor containerized services</li>
          <li><code>Nginx Proxy Manager</code> voor reverse proxy + Let’s Encrypt wildcard</li>
          <li><code>Portainer</code> voor container beheer (intern)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="box" style="margin-top:14px">
        <h3>Security highlights</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>SSH: public key auth</li>
          <li>Router: alleen TCP 80/443 naar NPM</li>
          <li>TLS: wildcard cert <code>*.dijkman.dev</code></li>
          <li>Hardening: security headers op proxy hosts</li>
          <li>Roadmap: access lists, Cloudflare, monitoring + backups</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
